label.value: abolished protein kinase activity in response to osmotic stress

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which a protein kinase activity is absent during a cellular response to  osmotic stress.

label.value: abolished protein kinase activity in response to oxidative stress

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which a protein kinase activity is absent during a cellular response to  oxidative stress.

definition.value: A transcription regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin silencing in at rDNA is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Chromatin silencing is the observed effect of processes that repress transcription in a region of the genome that is normally assembled into heterochromatin.

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphate (Pi) in the cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the total amount of phosphate (Pi) in the cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphate (Pi) measured in the cell is lower than normal.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the total amount of phosphate (Pi) measured in the cell is lower than normal.

label.value: increased H3-K56 acetylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 56 of histone H3 occurs to a higher extent than normal.
A molecular function phenotype in which the binding of a protein to a histone is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of histone H3 binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of histone H4 binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.
A metabolism phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which glutamate biosynthesis is abnormal.

definition.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a polyphosphatase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which a polyphosphatase activity is absent.

A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of 1,5-bisdiphospho-1D-myo-inositol 2,3,4,6-tetrakisphosphate (1,5-IP8) measured in a cell is higher than normal.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of 5-diphospho-1D-myo-inositol 1,2,3,4,6-pentakisphosphate (5-IP7) is higher than normal.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of 1-diphospho-1D-myo-inositol 2,3,4,5,6-pentakisphosphate (1-IP7) is higher than normal.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of myo-inositol measured in a cell is lower than normal.

A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of 1,5-bisdiphospho-1D-myo-inositol 2,3,4,6-tetrakisphosphate (1,5-IP8) measured in a cell is lower than normal.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of 5-diphospho-1D-myo-inositol 1,2,3,4,6-pentakisphosphate (5-IP7) is lower than normal.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of 1-diphospho-1D-myo-inositol 2,3,4,5,6-pentakisphosphate (1-IP7) is lower than normal.

definition.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of myo-inositol in a cell is normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of 5-diphospho-1D-myo-inositol 1,2,3,4,6-pentakisphosphate (5-IP7) is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of 1-diphospho-1D-myo-inositol 2,3,4,5,6-pentakisphosphate (1-IP7) is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to 1-chloro-2,4-dinitrobenzene (CDNB). Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of 1-chloro-2,4-dinitrobenzene that allows wild type cells to grow.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of a ceramide measured in a cell higher than normal.
A molecular function phenotype in which a guanyl-nucleotide exchange factor activity is abnormal.
A molecular function phenotype in which a guanyl-nucleotide exchange factor activity is absent.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of mitochondrial DNA present in the cell is higher than normal.

label.value: increased phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate level in the cell division site plasma membrane

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate measured in the cell division site plasma membrane is higher than normal.

label.value: protein mislocalized to cell division site

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a protein that is not normally found in the cell division site is observed there.

A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which Endoplasmic Reticulum tethering to the plasma membrane is normal. Normal ER to plasma membrane tethering results in correct localization of the ER.

A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to guanozole. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of guanozole that allows wild type cells to grow.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of 24-methylene lanosterol  measured in a cell is higher than normal.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of ergosta- 5,7,24(28)-trienol  measured in a cell is higher than normal.

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of ergosta-5,7-dienol measured in a cell is higher than normal.
ergosta-5,7-dienol level is not a normal pathway intermediate, but forms when Erg5 is inhibited.

label.value: decreased rate of protein exchange at plasma membrane

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of protein exchange between the plasma membrane and the cytosol is decreased.

label.value: abnormal punctate nuclear protein localization during meiotic prophase I

value.value: A cell phenotype observed during prophase of the first division of the meiotic cell cycle in which a protein that is normally localized to discrete regions in the nucleus, visible as foci or dots by microscopy, is abnormally localized.

label.value: decreased punctate nuclear protein localization during meiotic prophase I

value.value: A cell phenotype observed during prophase of the first division of the meiotic cell cycle in which a protein that is normally localized to discrete regions in the nucleus, visible as foci or dots by microscopy, is abnormally localized such that fewer dots are observed than in normal (wild type) cells.

label.value: abolished punctate nuclear protein localization during meiotic prophase I

value.value: A cell phenotype observed during prophase of the first division of the meiotic cell cycle in which the localization of a protein to discrete regions in the nucleus, visible as foci or dots by microscopy, is abolished.

label.value: normal number of Rad51 foci during meiotic prophase I

value.value: A cell phenotype observed during prophase of the first division of the meiotic cell cycle in which the number of sites at which the protein Rad51 accumulates is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abolished protein localization to nucleus during meiosis

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus during one or both meiotic nuclear divisions is abolished.
A cellular process phenotype in which the occurrence of meiotic recombination between alleles on different sister chromatids (inter-sister recombination) is increased.

label.value: increased mitotic DNA replication initiation from late origin

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the frequency of DNA replication initiation is higher than normal at layte origins.

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a cell divides with a smaller diameter than normal (i.e. compared to wild-type cells under the same conditions).
A cell phenotype in which a cell divides with a greater volume than normal (i.e. compared to wild-type cells under the same conditions).

label.value: increased cell surface area at division

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a cell divides with a greater surface area than normal (i.e. compared to wild-type cells under the same conditions).
A cell phenotype in which meiotic telomere clustering is unstable, leading to transient unclustering of telomeres.

label.value: normal protein localization to meiotic spindle pole body during prophase I

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the meiotic spindle pole body during prophase of the first meiotic nuclear division is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal meiotic spindle pole body insertion into nuclear envelope in meiosis I

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which insertion of the spindle pole body into the nuclear envelope during the first meiotic nuclear division is normal.
